148.6	Wendell_Berry	Wendell Berry	Wendell Berry (born August 5, 1934 Henry County, Kentucky) is an American man of letters, academic, cultural and economic critic, and farmer. He is a prolific author of novels, short stories, poems, and essays. He is also an elected member of the Fellowship of Southern Writers and a recipient of The National Humanities Medal.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/38/Wberry.jpg/220px-Wberry.jpg
